Text.SourceString: Well, hello… Nice to meet you. Call me <NPCName>Nina</>.
What should I call you?
Mother is such a hoarder. I’m constantly finding new things around the house.
I could sell the whole house, and I swear to you, new things would still keep popping up. Ha!
I just adore this island. They call themselves “islanders.” Oh, my heart! So adorbs.
The wild jackfruit is so sweet here. If you’re lucky, you might find some massive ones near the river.
Isn’t that spectacular?!
If you see anything you like at the villa, just let me know, darl. I can probably sell it to you.
I don’t need most of the items in my house. It’d be best for me to rehome the art and the furniture, but it really isn’t that simple.
I’m heading to Dulca Island for the Autumn. It’s the best time to visit if you’re interested… Then I’m probably going to spend the Winter with Mother.
Oh, yes, of course. They call it Fall here, not Autumn, don’t they? It’s the falling leaves season.
I have small yard sales sometimes. Trying to rehome the best of my collection. Interested?
I love the mayor. He’s like a father to me. Always makes sure that I feel welcome here. Like, who do you know with a better heart?!
No one, right?!
This place is the best in the Summer. Love, love, LOVE keeping up with my childhood friends. Surfing, staying up, chilling at the beach. What more is there to life?
I just adore this island. They call themselves “islanders.” Oh, my heart! So adorbs.
Coral Island feels the most like home to me. I feel like packing up and moving right back in, this Winter!
Is that impulsive? Maybe I should wait until Spring. I need to talk to Mother about it first, anyway… See what she thinks.
I have small yard sales sometimes. Trying to rehome the best of my collection. Interested?
How are you doing today, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>?
Remember, I’m rooting for you! Keep it up.
I don’t know what I’m rooting for just yet, but I am! Go, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Mother is such a hoarder. I’m constantly finding new things around the house.
I could sell the whole house, and I swear to you, new things would still keep popping up. Ha!
This place is the best in the Summer. Love, love, LOVE keeping up with my childhood friends. Surfing, staying up, chilling at the beach. What more is there to life?
I know Mother would tell me to do whatever makes me happy. But I really don’t want to leave her alone, now that Father is gone.
I’m all she’s got. I feel bad, but I also don’t want to force her to move here with me.
I’m heading to Dulca Island for the Autumn. It’s the best time to visit, if you’re interested… Then I’m probably going to spend the Winter with Mother.

I like to spend my Summers here, keeping up with my childhood friends. Surfing, staying up, chilling at the beach… What more is there to life?
Oh my… I’m debating whether I should move back here this coming Winter, or next year.
Maybe next year. Start off with a clean slate, you know…
I’m gonna be at the beach all day tomorrow. Probably head to the tavern afterward. Will you be there?
No promises, though. If I get too exhausted, then I’ll just go straight home.
If you see anything you like at the villa, just let me know, darl. I can probably sell it to you.

You don’t look like a busy farmer, darling. Everything’s okay at the farm, I hope?

Let me tell you something… I feel like I’m being watched sometimes. There’s an extra pair of eyes in the villa. I can feel it.
Ha ha… Never mind. I think I’ve been reading one too many mysteries.
Falling asleep with my windows open is the best. The sound of the ocean is so relaxing.
You know, living alone is not as bad as I thought it would be.
Sure, occasionally you get lonely, but sometimes it’s nice to just be by yourself, you know?
I should host a dinner party and invite all my friends. Would you come?
My oh my! Darling, you have to come. There will be plenty of food and music… New friends! It will be so much fun.
I hate to call the villa a “vacation home,” because it’s actually home in my eyes… Not some resort hotel.
My childhood friends are all here. This is where my parents had me. Mother planted flowers in this soil… And Father…
For my seventh birthday, Father got me a small patch of land over at Turtle Island. Our family uses it for berry planting.
Oh, nothing compared to your farm, doll! A watermelon to a blueberry! My patch of land is as small as my villa.
It’s berry season! Oh, I would love to visit a berry farm this time of year.
What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?

Happy Sunday to you!
I get confused when people ask me where I’m from. Coral Island is definitely home to me, so I always tell them that.
I was born here, for crying out loud. But the thing is, Mother is from the other side of the globe. So I don’t know if I actually count as a Coral Island native.
I hate to call the villa a “vacation home,” because it’s actually home in my eyes. Not some resort hotel.
My childhood friends are all here. This is where my parents raised me. Mother planted flowers on this soil. And Father…
And Father was laid to rest here.
Growing up, I felt like I didn’t resemble either of my parents. I know it’s nothing, but it made me feel like I didn’t fit in.
Thankfully none of the people here ever made me feel like my appearance matters too much. Family gatherings, though… Whew! My cousins would let me have it.

Spring cleaning is such a pain when you have a big house. It’s even worse when you have a mother who likes to buy so many things. Ugh.
I’m so glad it’s starting to get warmer. I was this close to packing up and moving somewhere else!
I’m so excited for Summer, darl. It’ll be so much fun!//<portrait=surprised>The food, the swimming, the beach, everything!
I hate Spring cleaning.//<portrait=surprised>I should ask <NPCName>Suki</> to do it. She LOVES Spring cleaning.
I tried going into the ocean the other day, and it was still too cold!//<portrait=concerned>Maybe I need to wait a few more days…
Oh, darl, it’s finally, finally getting warmer. I can feel the Summer vibes just around the corner!
I wonder what <NPCName>Suki</> is up to? Frantically cleaning the inn, probably.

Oh, I need to tell you a funny story about <NPCName>Luke</>. One time, we were hunting for ghosts by that temple near the villa. It was dark, and I snuck away from him while he walked around the temple.//I hid, and when he noticed I was gone, he kept calling my name over and over again.//<portrait=surprised>So then, I jumped out and scared him! He fell down and he cried and cried and cried!
Can’t believe that crybaby grew up to be so tall.
<NPCName>Walter</> and Father used to take <NPCName>Luke</> and me sailing the first weekend of every Summer.//<portrait=sad>Eventually, we stopped that tradition, and then Father, well…
Just look around us, darl. You can see why I always come back here in Summer, can’t you?
When I was younger, we didn’t always live here, but Father always made sure we came here for Summer. It’s his favorite place in the whole world.
Father was the one who taught me how to surf and sail. Well…not personally. He was too busy for that.//But he was the one pushing for lessons and camps.
The Beach Cleanup Festival is the main reason I love Summer so much.

When I was younger, Father and Mother took me to the beach almost every single day in Summer.//Father would play with me in the water, and Mother would make banana fritters.//<portrait=happy>We always finished the day with some corn on the cob from the cart. It was so much fun!
Do you think <NPCName>Luke</>  will still let me put flower crowns on him?//<portrait=normal>Probably not, huh?
Oh, do you happen to grow berries at your farm? I think Autumn is the perfect season for berry picking, don’t you?
I’m so <Italic>so</> sad Summer is over. Should I leave town again?//<portrait=happy>Just kidding! I think I’m gonna stay here for a while.
I forget how pretty Coral Island is in Autumn. It’s just so picturesque with all the falling leaves.
What do you call it, darl, Autumn or Fall?
Around this time of the year, Mother always made sure we were ready for our annual skiing trip.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m not very good at it… It never really <Italic>hooked</> me, as it were.
It’s getting cold, isn’t it?//<portrait=annoyed>Remind me again why I decided to move back here.
What should I do today?//The cold weather makes me lazy.
There’s something really beautiful about the beach in Winter, isn’t there?
Oh, darling, how do you stay so active in Winter? It’s so cold!
I can’t wait for the New Year’s Eve Festival!//<portrait=normal>I definitely missed it when I moved away.
We need to keep hydrated, always… Especially in Winter when it’s dry like this.
<NPCName>Bree’s</> parties are always so much fun, aren’t they? Nowhere near as much fun as Mother’s, of course. It’s too bad you haven’t been to any.
I’m so tempted to spend the Winter somewhere warmer.//<portrait=happy>Want to join me sometime?
I’m not technically new here.//oh no no!//My family used to live in Coral Island until Mother decided to leave some time ago.
Now I spend my Summers here, catching up with old friends…and making new ones along the way.
I tried to get Mother to spend the Summer here with me. Just this one time, you know… I didn’t want to come alone. But she refused.
She prefers cold winds, she said. No use trying to talk Mother into anything. Fine by me…
So, tell me. What have you learned about farming so far?
What a fun, simple life! I need to get me one of those. Oh, it’s just so tiring to always move from place to place, never feeling at home.
The villa is too big for me to stay in. But I know Mother would be outraged if I swapped it for a modest-sized cabin.
I could never, anyway. It’s my childhood home. There’s no way I can ever destroy or sell the villa.
The villa is too big for me to stay in. But I know Mother would be outraged if I swapped it for a modest-sized cabin.
I could never, anyway. It’s my childhood home. There’s no way I can ever destroy or sell the villa.
I’ll be here next Summer. Why wouldn’t I be? I would miss it too much.
It would be such fun to stay for Autumn! But I can’t… Ugh!
I need to pack tomorrow. I’m bringing back some antiques and wine for Mother.
Oh my! What a fun Summer! I just absolutely love it here.
Ah, the wind is nice and breezy today!
We got just what we needed.
This may sound a bit silly, but I’m curious about the forest. I heard there are monsters in the cavern?
I’m afraid if I go to the forest alone, I might get lost and run into one of those monsters.
Ha ha ha. Silly, I know.
The leaves are solid brown now. It’s a sign that the trees will start losing leaves soon.
The weather definitely changed, but not enough to need a sweater.//I’m fine, thanks for asking.
I got my party planning gene from Mother.//My family used to have parties where Mother would invite everybody on the island for my birthday.
I never really understood why, because honestly it was more tiring to me than anything. And I always had to wear some itchy dress… I hated those. But the parties, though… They were out of this world.
Oh, how I miss the sound of waves in the Winter! I just spend the day curled up under a blanket.
Mother always insisted that we go skiing in the Winter, because you can do everything else any other time, according to her.//But skiing can only be done in the Winter.
She’s not wrong, but it doesn’t make it right. I mean, every Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>? Skiing? Come on!
The one time I’m here, it rains.
The one time I’m here, it rains.
Your boots are soaked! It must be raining hard outside, huh?
Humph. Oh well… It’s only water, right? So what if it’s a little muddy?
The one time that I’m here, it rains like this.
Bad luck, I suppose.
Oh my! Was that thunder I just heard?
Humph. Oh well… The rain is only water, right? So what if it’s a little muddy and thundery?
Oh, this rain isn’t going to stop me from leaving my house.
It’s just a little bit of water.
This place hasn’t changed. I love it.
Father used to take me here after hours to get a treat.
I suppose it doesn’t matter how far away I go. I always belong here…
Close to Father.
My dad worked long hours at home, and there was a period when he didn’t come out of his office at all for days at a time.
It was a really bad habit of his… Overworking himself. Then he would take me here for father-daughter time to make up for the time he spent working.
Did I really call him “Dad”? Hah! That’s new.
You come here to dance, don’t you? You look like the dancing type.
Come on! Show me what you’ve got.
Father would flip if he knew that I cut my hair short like this!
Ha! Kidding. He wouldn’t! Father wouldn’t care. He would literally let me do whatever I wanted… And I did.//Mother was angry every time I threw dinner plates across the table. But not Father.
“Helena, she’s just a child… Just a plate, we still have plenty…” Blah blah blah.//A monster...I was.
This volleyball court wasn’t here last year. I wonder if this was Pufferfish’s doing as well.
Up for a game of volleyball?
I suppose it doesn’t matter how far away I go. I always belong here…
Close to Father.
I don’t see kids building elaborate sandcastles anymore.
I suppose it may be a different era now.
Wait, are you joking? You don’t know how to sail?
So when you were in school, what did you do during your Summer breaks, if not sailing?
I would invite you in, but the house still smells a bit musty.
Maybe next time…
It’s great to be back.
I haven’t spent a Winter here in so long.
Oh, gosh, I hope the heat still works.
I don’t need most of the items here… My family has so much unnecessary stuff.
This stuff is unused and probably bored, sitting around with nobody paying attention to it.
Ah, I rarely spend my days at home… The whole living alone thing gets boring fast, so I come here instead.
You know how it is, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re all alone on that farm too. Or do you have company?
I learned to sail a long time ago, when I was <NPCName>Valentina</>'s age. Father sent me to a Summer camp where I also learned to scuba dive.
I’m not a big diver, but it did add some heft to my college application.//It came in handy at cocktail parties… So I’m grateful.
Wait, are you joking? You don’t know how to sail?
So when you were in school, what did you do during your Summer breaks, if not sailing?
